body:
#### PR description:

* As discussed with @fabiocos, a numbering scheme may need to use extra information encoded in a node name. 
* The new `geoHistory()` implementation gives direct access to the nodes in a reverse order:
```
Tracker[1]/CMSE[1]/OCMS[1]/
[1]/[1]/[1]/
0/0/0/
```
Here is an example on how to extract such information without the need to parse the path to the node:

```c++
cms::DDFilter filter("TrackingMaterialGroup", {i.data(), i.size()});
cms::DDFilteredView fv(*cpv, filter);
bool firstChild = fv.firstChild();
const std::vector<const cms::Node*> nodes = fv.geoHistory();
for(const auto& n : nodes) {
  log << n->GetVolume()->GetName() << "[" << n->GetNumber() << "]/";
 }
const auto nodeCopyNums = fv.copyNumbers();
for(const auto& c : nodeCopyNums) {
  log << "[" << c << "]/";
}
const auto navPos = fv.navPos();
for(const auto& p : navPos) {
  log << p << "/";
}
```
